<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>What is martial arts scheduling software?</h3>

<p>Martial arts scheduling software is a specialised platform for managing class schedules, private lessons, seminars, and instructor availability at martial arts schools. It includes features like belt-level class restrictions, capacity management, and attendance tracking that generic scheduling tools lack.</p>

<h3>How does belt-level scheduling work?</h3>

<p>Belt-level scheduling automatically filters which classes students can book based on their current rank. A white belt sees only beginner-appropriate classes, while advanced students see their eligible options. This prevents mismatched skill levels in classes and ensures appropriate training progression.</p>

<h3>Can I manage multiple locations with one system?</h3>

<p>Yes, quality martial arts scheduling software supports multi-location operations. Each location maintains its own schedule while sharing student databases, allowing students to book across locations and providing consolidated reporting for owners.</p>

<h3>How do private lesson bookings work?</h3>

<p>Students view instructor availability calendars, select available time slots, and book directly with payment. The system manages instructor calendars, sends confirmations and reminders, and tracks prepaid lesson packages. Cancellation policies can be enforced automatically.</p>

<h3>Can students book classes online?</h3>

<p>Yes, students can view real-time schedules, see available spots, and book directly through web portals or mobile apps. Booking confirmations, reminders, and calendar integration happen automatically.</p>

<h3>How does the waitlist feature work?</h3>

<p>When a class reaches capacity, additional booking attempts go to a waitlist. If a registered student cancels, the first waitlisted student receives automatic notification and can claim the spot. Priority waitlist options can favour certain membership types.</p>

<h3>What reports can I generate?</h3>

<p>Scheduling reports include class attendance by time slot, instructor performance metrics, capacity utilisation rates, no-show tracking, and historical attendance trends. These insights help optimise your schedule for maximum effectiveness.</p>

<h3>Does scheduling software integrate with billing?</h3>

<p>Integrated platforms connect scheduling with billing, enabling private lesson payment at booking, seminar registration fees, membership validation for class access, and tracking of included vs. additional classes based on membership type.</p>

